article.headline: Siena 77, Canisius 49
article.story: ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) -- Edwin Ubiles scored 20 points, grabbed eight rebounds and had five assists to lead Siena to a 77-49 win over Canisius Monday night in the Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference. The conference-leading Saints (12-6, 7-1 MAAC) committed just four turnovers in picking up their fourth straight win, holding Canisius to under 40 percent shooting from the field. Chris De La Rosa scored 10 points and had five assists in 22 minutes off the bench for Siena. He made all four of his field goal attempts and collected three of Siena's 13 steals. Frank Turner scored nine of his 15 points in the first half to pace Canisius (3-15, 1-7). Rishawn Johnson had 11 points and four rebounds in 23 minutes off the bench. Siena used an 11-0 run to push its lead to 30, the biggest of the game, seven minutes into the second half.
